Most Important Interview Insight

Two Sum teaches:

complement technique
hashing
two pointer strategy
frequency counting
pair problems
foundation of KSum family

This is why it is one of the most important DSA patterns.

The pattern is:

2Sum → two pointers or hashmap
3Sum → fix one number, then solve 2Sum on the rest of the array
4Sum → fix two numbers, then solve 2Sum
KSum → recursively fix numbers until k == 2

Easy Pattern to Remember
2Sum  -> two pointers
3Sum  -> fix 1, solve 2Sum
4Sum  -> fix 2, solve 2Sum
KSum  -> fix one recursively, base case is 2Sum

Why duplicate skipping is needed at every level

Imagine the array contains repeated values like 0, 0.

At a given recursion level, if you choose the first 0 and then again choose the second 0 as the first number at that same level, you may generate the same combinations twice.

So at every recursive level, you skip duplicates among siblings in the same loop.

That is exactly what this check does.